<span id="freeTextContainer9088556230245910713">Although Tillich&apos;s writing can seem frustratingly academic, the ideas he presents are extremely relevant. He provides a historical framework on the philosophy of courage from Plato to Spinoza and then uses that platform to posit his own reasoning as a religious philosophic. Give this some time to sink in. It&apos;s worth it.<br/><br/>Do not read this unless you have some momentum going already.</span>
  <span id="freeText9088556230245910713" style="display:none">Although Tillich's writing can seem frustratingly academic, the ideas he presents are extremely relevant. He provides a historical framework on the philosophy of courage from Plato to Spinoza and then uses that platform to posit his own reasoning as a religious philosophic. Give this some time to sink in. It's worth it.<br /><br />Do not read this unless you have some momentum going already.</span>
