<div id="review_1117264127" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1117264127" />
    <a title="Mack Hayden" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6036690-mack-hayden"><img alt="Mack Hayden" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498610629p2/6036690.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1117264127?book_show_action=true">Sep 06, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mack Hayden" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mack Hayden" href="/user/show/6036690-mack-hayden">Mack Hayden</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6036690-mack-hayden?shelf=philosophy">philosophy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6036690-mack-hayden?shelf=religion">religion</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1117264127" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14003692998170726237">This is one hell of a book, compadres. I don&apos;t think I&apos;ve ever read something that so concisely and incisively describes the history of man&apos;s existential anxieties and the ways he&apos;s tried to deaden or cure them. It&apos;d be wildly impressive simply as an overview, but the fact Tillich&apos;s own commentary is so eloquent and straight-for-the-jugular makes it doubly so. If you spend any time worrying and wondering about the situation we humans have found ourselves in, I really think you owe it to yourself</span>
  <span id="freeText14003692998170726237" style="display:none">This is one hell of a book, compadres. I don't think I've ever read something that so concisely and incisively describes the history of man's existential anxieties and the ways he's tried to deaden or cure them. It'd be wildly impressive simply as an overview, but the fact Tillich's own commentary is so eloquent and straight-for-the-jugular makes it doubly so. If you spend any time worrying and wondering about the situation we humans have found ourselves in, I really think you owe it to yourself to give this a read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14003692998170726237" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

